trend_summary: Across the sequence, farmland and forested pockets are gradually replaced by light-industrial blocks, retail pads and a few new housing clusters. Built space spreads mainly along the highway corridors, while green areas persist in golf course and river buffer zones. Overall footprint grows moderately, indicating incremental suburban densification rather than wholesale urbanisation.
notable_changes: Enlargement of industrial park parcels in the southwest and near the northern interchange.
New commercial/retail buildings appear around major highway junctions, replacing fields.
